Cat Skiing at Sharr Mountains

Nord Freeride Cat-Skiing

Most affordable Catskiing in Europe, Catskiing in Kosovo covering 40+ (descents) Skiing and Snowboarding fresh powder slopes (7km+ each run) within Sharr Mountains with elevating peaks as high as 2658m, Grand Rudoka (2658m) is the highest peak in Kosovo. Powder skiing in Europe (Balkans). Freeride skiing in Europe, Off piste skiing in Europe, backcountry skiing in Europe, you name it!

Almost all of our runs (95%+) are faced on the North side (See 3D Google Pics/runs below) therefore the quality of the snow is unique. We receive numerous major storms, which grants us reliable snow from Mid December to late April. The cat-skiing terrain at Nord Freeride is gigantic and covers more than 100 square kilometers, with daily 4500m+ of vertical descents at such a wide terrain, freeride and backcountry skiing options are unlimited here, every day new and untouched slope, so get ready to tighten up your sleeves and hit all our fresh powder slopes.

Also, our food is special, everything is organic (meet, dairy, fruits, vegetables, vine, alcohol etc) from 2000m+ heights.

Nord Freeride lodge (1550m) is just north from Restelice Village (go to Terms & Conditions for more info), and only 1.5 hours drive from Prishtina International (Kosovo) airport, Snowcat will wait you at the doorsteps of the Lodge every morning so you can shred slopes from peaks as high as 2658m.

Come and join this unforgettable journey!

Winter is coming!

Cat Skiing Runs

At Nord Freeride Powder is what we have in every single day from unlimited large open bowl to steep powder runs, most of our runs are 7+ kilometres per ride, we even have our longest run which is 11+ km, please see all the Google 3D pics for more info, all the descends are exact and can be confirmed on 3D Google maps.
 
The red lines represent each run, there would be around 7+ long runs daily, every day new and untouched slope!
